[
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688405",
        "quote": "The preacher's sharpest and strongest preaching should be to himself. His most difficult, delicate, laborious, and thorough work must be with himself.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688405"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Work",
                "url": "/topics/work"
            },
            {
                "name": "Delicate",
                "url": "/topics/delicate"
            },
            {
                "name": "Laborious",
                "url": "/topics/laborious"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688415",
        "quote": "It is only when the whole heart is gripped with the passion of prayer that the life-giving fire descends, for none but the earnest man gets access to the ear of God.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688415"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Whole",
                "url": "/topics/whole"
            },
            {
                "name": "Access",
                "url": "/topics/access"
            },
            {
                "name": "None",
                "url": "/topics/none"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688411",
        "quote": "The resurrection of Jesus Christ was necessary to establish the truth of his mission and put the stamp of all-conquering power on his gospel.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688411"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Christ",
                "url": "/topics/christ"
            },
            {
                "name": "Stamp",
                "url": "/topics/stamp"
            },
            {
                "name": "Necessary",
                "url": "/topics/necessary"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688412",
        "quote": "The most casual reader of the New Testament can scarcely fail to see the commanding position the resurrection of Christ holds in Christianity. It is the creator of its new and brighter hopes, of its richer and stronger faith, of its deeper and more exalted experience.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688412"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Faith",
                "url": "/topics/faith"
            },
            {
                "name": "Christianity",
                "url": "/topics/christianity"
            },
            {
                "name": "Reader",
                "url": "/topics/reader"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688423",
        "quote": "The houses of Heaven are God-built and are as enduring and incorruptible as their builder. We will have bodies after the resurrection; transfigured they will be after the model of Christ's glorious body.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688423"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Will",
                "url": "/topics/will"
            },
            {
                "name": "Christ",
                "url": "/topics/christ"
            },
            {
                "name": "Enduring",
                "url": "/topics/enduring"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688435",
        "quote": "It must never be forgotten that Almighty God rules this world. He is not an absentee God.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688435"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "World",
                "url": "/topics/world"
            },
            {
                "name": "Never",
                "url": "/topics/never"
            },
            {
                "name": "Almighty God",
                "url": "/topics/almighty_god"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688408",
        "quote": "The life-giving preacher is a man of God, whose heart is ever athirst for God, whose soul is ever following hard after God, whose eye is single to God, and in whom by the power of God's Spirit the flesh and the world have been crucified, and his ministry is like the generous flood of a life-giving river.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688408"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Soul",
                "url": "/topics/soul"
            },
            {
                "name": "World",
                "url": "/topics/world"
            },
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688414",
        "quote": "Woe to the generation of sons who find their censers empty of the rich incense of prayer, whose fathers have been too busy or too unbelieving to pray, and perils inexpressible and consequences untold are their unhappy heritage.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688414"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            },
            {
                "name": "Woe",
                "url": "/topics/woe"
            },
            {
                "name": "Fathers",
                "url": "/topics/fathers"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688420",
        "quote": "The transfiguration of Jesus is one of the typical facts of the resurrection of the body; not only of the glorious change, but of the renewed life of the body and of the general judgment day.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688420"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Change",
                "url": "/topics/change"
            },
            {
                "name": "Body",
                "url": "/topics/body"
            },
            {
                "name": "Facts",
                "url": "/topics/facts"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688407",
        "quote": "Preaching is God's great institution for the planting and maturing of spiritual life. When properly executed, its benefits are untold; when wrongly executed, no evil can exceed its damaging results.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688407"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Spiritual Life",
                "url": "/topics/spiritual_life"
            },
            {
                "name": "Benefits",
                "url": "/topics/benefits"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688431",
        "quote": "Prayer is a specific divine appointment, an ordinance of Heaven, whereby God purposes to carry out His gracious designs on earth and to execute and make efficient the plan of salvation.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688431"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Salvation",
                "url": "/topics/salvation"
            },
            {
                "name": "Efficient",
                "url": "/topics/efficient"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688438",
        "quote": "Prayer concerns God, whose purposes and plans are conditioned on prayer. His will and His glory are bound up in praying.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688438"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Will",
                "url": "/topics/will"
            },
            {
                "name": "Bound",
                "url": "/topics/bound"
            },
            {
                "name": "Concerns",
                "url": "/topics/concerns"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688450",
        "quote": "Prayer must be broad in its scope - it must plead for others. Intercession for others is the hallmark of all true prayer. When prayer is confined to self and to the sphere of one's personal needs, it dies by reason of its littleness, narrowness and selfishness.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688450"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Reason",
                "url": "/topics/reason"
            },
            {
                "name": "Needs",
                "url": "/topics/needs"
            },
            {
                "name": "Hallmark",
                "url": "/topics/hallmark"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688437",
        "quote": "The life of the individual believer, his personal salvation, and personal Christian graces have their being, bloom and fruitage in prayer.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688437"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Individual",
                "url": "/topics/individual"
            },
            {
                "name": "Salvation",
                "url": "/topics/salvation"
            },
            {
                "name": "Being",
                "url": "/topics/being"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688429",
        "quote": "We may excuse the spiritual poverty of our preaching in many ways, but the true secret will be found in the lack of urgent prayer for God's presence in the power of the Holy Spirit.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688429"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "May",
                "url": "/topics/may"
            },
            {
                "name": "Will",
                "url": "/topics/will"
            },
            {
                "name": "Holy",
                "url": "/topics/holy"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688401",
        "quote": "In the Bible, we have the facts and history of man's redemption. Incidentally or essentially, other worlds and other beings are brought prominently on the stage of redemption purposes and plans.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688401"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Bible",
                "url": "/topics/bible"
            },
            {
                "name": "Worlds",
                "url": "/topics/worlds"
            },
            {
                "name": "Other",
                "url": "/topics/other"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688402",
        "quote": "The Bible nowhere enters into an argument to prove the person and being of God. It assumes His being and reveals His person and character.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688402"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Bible",
                "url": "/topics/bible"
            },
            {
                "name": "Argument",
                "url": "/topics/argument"
            },
            {
                "name": "Assumes",
                "url": "/topics/assumes"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688403",
        "quote": "Bible revelations are not against reason but above reason, for the uses of faith, man's highest faculty.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688403"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Bible",
                "url": "/topics/bible"
            },
            {
                "name": "Reason",
                "url": "/topics/reason"
            },
            {
                "name": "Highest",
                "url": "/topics/highest"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688404",
        "quote": "A denial of the reality of demonical possessions on the part of anyone who believes the Gospel narrative to be true and inspired may justly be regarded as simply and plainly inconceivable.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688404"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "May",
                "url": "/topics/may"
            },
            {
                "name": "Denial",
                "url": "/topics/denial"
            },
            {
                "name": "Inconceivable",
                "url": "/topics/inconceivable"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688406",
        "quote": "Every preacher who does not make prayer a mighty factor in his own life and ministry is weak as a factor in God's work and is powerless to project God's cause in this world.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688406"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Work",
                "url": "/topics/work"
            },
            {
                "name": "Project",
                "url": "/topics/project"
            },
            {
                "name": "Own",
                "url": "/topics/own"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688409",
        "quote": "Faith accepts the Bible as the word and will of God and rests upon its truth without question and without other evidence.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688409"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Bible",
                "url": "/topics/bible"
            },
            {
                "name": "Question",
                "url": "/topics/question"
            },
            {
                "name": "Other",
                "url": "/topics/other"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688410",
        "quote": "The Scriptures bear ample and continuous evidence that the faith of the resurrection of the body lies in the faith that Jesus Christ died and rose again.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688410"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Evidence",
                "url": "/topics/evidence"
            },
            {
                "name": "Christ",
                "url": "/topics/christ"
            },
            {
                "name": "Again",
                "url": "/topics/again"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688413",
        "quote": "The more praying there is in the world, the better the world will be, the mightier the forces against evil everywhere.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688413"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "World",
                "url": "/topics/world"
            },
            {
                "name": "Better",
                "url": "/topics/better"
            },
            {
                "name": "Will",
                "url": "/topics/will"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688416",
        "quote": "Man's access in prayer to God opens everything and makes his impoverishment his wealth. All things are his through prayer.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688416"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Wealth",
                "url": "/topics/wealth"
            },
            {
                "name": "Through",
                "url": "/topics/through"
            },
            {
                "name": "Access",
                "url": "/topics/access"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688417",
        "quote": "Faith can make no appeal to reason or the fitness of things; its appeal is to the Word of God, and whatever is therein revealed, faith accepts as true.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688417"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Reason",
                "url": "/topics/reason"
            },
            {
                "name": "Accepts",
                "url": "/topics/accepts"
            },
            {
                "name": "Therein",
                "url": "/topics/therein"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688418",
        "quote": "Christianity is not rationalism, but faith in God's revelation. A conspicuous, all-important item in that revelation is the resurrection of the body.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688418"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Faith",
                "url": "/topics/faith"
            },
            {
                "name": "Christianity",
                "url": "/topics/christianity"
            },
            {
                "name": "Item",
                "url": "/topics/item"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688421",
        "quote": "The strong argument for Heaven as a place centers in and clusters about Jesus. The man Jesus, bearing a man's form, the body He wore on earth, has a place assigned Him - a high place.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688421"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Strong",
                "url": "/topics/strong"
            },
            {
                "name": "Argument",
                "url": "/topics/argument"
            },
            {
                "name": "Bearing",
                "url": "/topics/bearing"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688422",
        "quote": "The glorified will not be pilgrims, transient visitors, or tenants at will, but settled, permanent, walled, established by title, through eternity by warrantee deed, signed, sealed, recorded, possession given. No renters, no lessees of Heaven, but all property and home owners.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688422"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Through",
                "url": "/topics/through"
            },
            {
                "name": "Possession",
                "url": "/topics/possession"
            },
            {
                "name": "Owners",
                "url": "/topics/owners"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688424",
        "quote": "Safety is in Heaven. Put your values there only; put your heart there. No tears are there to flood your heart, no sorrows there to break it, no losses there to grieve and embitter.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688424"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Values",
                "url": "/topics/values"
            },
            {
                "name": "Tears",
                "url": "/topics/tears"
            },
            {
                "name": "Break",
                "url": "/topics/break"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688425",
        "quote": "God's plan is to make much of the man, far more of him than of anything else. Men are God's method. The Church is looking for better methods; God is looking for better men.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688425"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "More",
                "url": "/topics/more"
            },
            {
                "name": "Methods",
                "url": "/topics/methods"
            },
            {
                "name": "Method",
                "url": "/topics/method"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688426",
        "quote": "The Holy Ghost does not flow through methods, but through men. He does not come on machinery, but on men. He does not anoint plans, but men - men of prayer.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688426"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Through",
                "url": "/topics/through"
            },
            {
                "name": "Methods",
                "url": "/topics/methods"
            },
            {
                "name": "Holy",
                "url": "/topics/holy"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688427",
        "quote": "The character as well as the fortunes of the gospel is committed to the preacher. He makes or mars the message from God to man. The preacher is the golden pipe through which the divine oil flows.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688427"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Through",
                "url": "/topics/through"
            },
            {
                "name": "Which",
                "url": "/topics/which"
            },
            {
                "name": "Committed",
                "url": "/topics/committed"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688428",
        "quote": "Preaching is not the performance of an hour. It is the outflow of a life. It takes twenty years to make a sermon because it takes twenty years to make the man. The true sermon is a thing of life. The sermon grows because the man grows.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688428"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Life",
                "url": "/topics/life"
            },
            {
                "name": "Grows",
                "url": "/topics/grows"
            },
            {
                "name": "Preaching",
                "url": "/topics/preaching"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688430",
        "quote": "The preachers who gain mighty results for God are the men who have prevailed in their pleadings with God ere venturing to plead with men.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688430"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Gain",
                "url": "/topics/gain"
            },
            {
                "name": "Prevailed",
                "url": "/topics/prevailed"
            },
            {
                "name": "Plead",
                "url": "/topics/plead"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688432",
        "quote": "When we say that prayer puts God to work, it is simply to say that man has it in his power by prayer to move God to work in His own way among men, in which way He would not work if prayer was not made.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688432"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Work",
                "url": "/topics/work"
            },
            {
                "name": "Move",
                "url": "/topics/move"
            },
            {
                "name": "Which",
                "url": "/topics/which"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688433",
        "quote": "If prayer puts God to work on earth, then, by the same token, prayerlessness rules God out of the world's affairs and prevents Him from working.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688433"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Work",
                "url": "/topics/work"
            },
            {
                "name": "Rules",
                "url": "/topics/rules"
            },
            {
                "name": "Prevents",
                "url": "/topics/prevents"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688434",
        "quote": "Prayer lays hold upon God and influences Him to work. This is the meaning of prayer as it concerns God. This is the doctrine of prayer, or else there is nothing whatever in prayer.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Edward McKendree Bounds",
            "url": "/quotes/edward_mckendree_bounds_688434"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Work",
                "url": "/topics/work"
